  "mixStrategy": "This relaxation Hip Hop score in Dm uses a i \u2192 iv \u2192 bVI \u2192 bVII progression (Dm \u2192 Gm \u2192 Bb \u2192 C) cycling every ~8 bars (~7.87s per cycle, roughly 5.5 cycles in 45s). The three tracks occupy distinct frequency bands to avoid masking:\n\nBASS (Synth Bass 38, 20-300Hz): Anchors the sub-low end with long sustained 808-style notes on chord roots \u2014 D2, G2, Bb1, C2. Notes are 3-4 seconds long with moderate velocity (85-100), providing the warm, heavy foundation. Locks to the harmonic rhythm.\n\nCHORDS (Warm Pad 89, 300Hz-2kHz): Dark minor pad voicings in the C3-C5 range. Each chord is a full voicing (root-3rd-5th or root-3rd-5th-7th) sustained for the full chord duration. Velocity is soft (35-50) to create a floating, atmospheric bed. Voicings use close position to stay warm and not too bright.\n\nMELODY (Vibraphone 11, 1kHz-8kHz): Bell-like motifs in C4-C6 range using D minor pentatonic (D-F-G-A-C). Notes sit slightly behind the beat with medium sustains (1-3s). Motifs are sparse and looping, targeting chord tones on strong beats. Velocity 45-65, rising in the middle energy arc and falling at the end.\n\nEnergy arc: Segments 1-6 (~7.5s each): 0.3\u21920.5\u21920.6\u21920.7\u21920.6\u21920.4. The piece opens sparse and quiet, builds gently to a peak around 22-30s, then recedes. Bass stays steady throughout; chords gradually fill out; melody introduces more notes in the middle then thins. All tracks change chords together on the same beats, creating a unified harmonic movement. The overall feel is dark, moody, spacious \u2014 perfect for late-night relaxation.",
